.TH RIGZ 1 "January 2026" "rigz 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rigz \- fast parallel gzip compression
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rigz
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rigz
is a high-performance, parallel gzip implementation that provides 40-50%
faster compression than gzip and pigz. It is a drop-in replacement for gzip
with a compatible command-line interface.
.PP
When invoked as
.B unrigz
or with the
.B \-d
option, rigz decompresses files.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-stdout
Write output to standard output; keep original files unchanged.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-decompress
Decompress the compressed input.
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-force
Force compression or decompression even if the file has multiple links
or the corresponding file already exists.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-k, \-\-keep
Keep (don't delete) input files during compression or decompression.
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-list
List compressed file contents.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-no-name
Do not save or restore the original file name and timestamp.
.TP
.B \-N, \-\-name
Save or restore the original file name and timestamp.
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-processes \fINUM\fR
Use NUM parallel processes for compression. Default is the number of
available CPU cores.
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Suppress all warnings.
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-recursive
Operate recursively on directories.
.TP
.B \-S, \-\-suffix \fISUFFIX\fR
Use SUFFIX instead of .gz.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-test
Test compressed file integrity.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Verbose mode. Display the name and percentage reduction for each file.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Display version number and exit.
.TP
.B \-1 ... \-9
Set compression level. \-1 (fastest) to \-9 (best compression).
Default is \-6.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Compress a file:
.B rigz file.txt
.TP
Decompress a file:
.B rigz -d file.txt.gz
.TP
Compress to stdout using 8 threads:
.B rigz -c -p8 file.txt > file.txt.gz
.TP
Decompress and keep original:
.B rigz -dk file.txt.gz
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Successful completion.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred.
.SH COMPATIBILITY
rigz produces output that is fully compatible with standard gzip. Files
compressed with rigz can be decompressed by any gzip implementation, and
rigz can decompress any standard gzip file.
.PP
The parallel compression works by creating multiple gzip "members" that
are concatenated together. This is valid per RFC 1952 and all standard
gzip implementations will correctly decompress such files.
